Sabres Beat Flyers, Predators Defeat Ducks in NHL Stanley Cup Playoffs

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-04-23T05:31:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-23/sabres-beat-flyers-predators-defeat-ducks-in-nhl-stanley-cup-playoffs.html
The  Buffalo Sabres  and the
Nashville Predators snapped ties to take 3-2 leads in their
National Hockey League Stanley Cup playoff series.  The Sabres defeated the Philadelphia Flyers 4-3, while the
Predators beat the Anaheim Ducks 4-3. Both games went into
overtime.  At Wells Fargo Center in Philadelphia, Tyler Ennis scored
his second goal of the game at five minutes, 31 seconds into
overtime to put the Sabres one game away from winning their
best-of-seven series. Ennis, Thomas Vanek and Marc-Andre Gragnani scored in the first period.  Danny Briere, James van Riemsdyk and Andrej Meszaros scored
for the Flyers, who travel to Buffalo for Game 6 tomorrow.  At Honda Center in Anaheim,  California , Jerred Smithson
scored a goal one minute, 57 seconds into overtime to give the
Predators the win. Kevin Klein, Joel Ward and Shea Weber scored
during regulation.  Jason Blake scored two goals and Jason Blake added a third
for the Ducks, who travel to Nashville April 24 for Game 6.  In todayâ€™s games, the  Pittsburgh Penguins  can advance to
round two with a win over the Tampa Bay Lightning; the
Washington Capitals will try to eliminate the New York Rangers;
the Montreal Canadiens or Boston Bruins will go a game up in
their 2-2 series; and the  San Jose Sharks  can knock out the  Los
Angeles Kings  with a victory.  To contact the reporter on this story:
